### Why `config.py` is built this way

| Decision | Reason |
|---|---|
| `pydantic_settings.BaseSettings` | Auto-reads `.env`, type-validates every field at startup |
| Single `settings` singleton | All modules import one instance — no scattered `os.getenv()` calls |
| `validate_settings()` | Catches missing keys immediately at startup, not mid-request |
| `LLM_TEMPERATURE=0.0` | Deterministic answers — critical for Q&A, not creative generation |
| `extra="ignore"` | Won't crash if `.env` has extra keys from other tools |

